n of the interaction of materials in certain high-temperature superconductors. He said that research on superconductivity is being actively pursued at his institute and elsewhere in the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION>. In a presentation Sunday, <PERSON> Mikhail </PERSON> <PERSON> V. </PERSON> <PERSON> Ivanov </PERSON>, director of the <ORGANIZATION> Institute </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> for </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Microbiology </ORGANIZATION>, said that the Soviet union has built industrial plants for the production of animal feed through yeast fermentation. Bacteria are being used to leach metals from poor quality ores, to decrease potentially dangerous levels of methane gas in coal mines and to enhance oil recovery, <PERSON> Ivanov </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Albert </PERSON> <PERSON> Galeev </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> Institute </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> for </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Space </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Research </ORGANIZATION> described the planned launch in July of a spacecraft to study the Martian moon Phobos, which may be an asteroid that got trapped in orbit around <LOCATION> Mars </LOCATION>.
