LOCATION> <LOCATION> Geneva </LOCATION> arms negotiator <PERSON> Max </PERSON> <PERSON> Friedersdorf </PERSON> as saying the agreement might not extend beyond <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON>'s term in office. <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Gen. <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Galvin </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> NATO </ORGANIZATION>'s chief commander in <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION>, told a West German newspaper on Saturday that he favored stationing the new weapons in <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION> `` where the troops are.''
