y <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hampshire </LOCATION> voters with telephones were interviewed, the results of these polls would vary by 6 percentage points simply because of chance variations in the sample. For polls based on aout 500 interviews _ like the <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> survey _ the sampling error margin is 5 percentage points. For polls based on about 600 interviews _ like the <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> survey _ the sampling error margin is 4 percentage points.
